SELECT \n    CASE \n        WHEN rn = 1 THEN 'A'\n        WHEN rn = 2 THEN 'B'\n        WHEN rn = 3 THEN 'C'\n        WHEN rn = 4 THEN 'D'\n        ELSE ''\n    END AS CharSeq,\n    id,\n    descr \nFROM (\n    SELECT \n        (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM mytable AS t2 WHERE t2.id <= t1.id) AS rn,\n        t1.id,\n        t1.descr\n    FROM mytable AS t1\n) AS numbered\nWHERE rn <= 4\nUNION\nSELECT '', id, descr \nFROM (\n    SELECT \n        (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM mytable AS t2 WHERE t2.id <= t1.id) AS rn,\n        t1.id,\n        t1.descr\n    FROM mytable AS t1\n) AS numbered\nWHERE rn > 4\nORDER BY id;